# Vault Priority (Claude-aligned)

For any non-trivial task (planning, feature work, bugfixes, refactors, API/schema/dashboard changes), treat `docs/vault/` as the canonical project source of truth.

## Required bootstrap

At task start, read:

1. `docs/vault/README.md`
2. `docs/vault/product/status.md`

Then use relevant vault notes (`architecture/*`, `entities/*`, `runbooks/*`, `adr/*`) before implementation decisions.

## Conflict resolution

If implementation details conflict with older docs outside vault, prefer `docs/vault/*` and treat non-vault historical docs as archival context only.

## Completion contract

If behavior/contracts/architecture changed, update relevant `docs/vault/*` notes (including `docs/vault/product/status.md` when applicable) in the same task.
